What exactly do you plan on doing with this variable? Depending on the circumstances I would use a HashMap like Darq said.For example, if the variable is to broadcast a specific message for elevated users on login, I would do this:public class GreetUsers extends JavaPlugin implements Listener {     Server server = Bukkit.getServer();    HashMap<String, Boolean> greet;     public void onEnable() {        this.greet = new HashMap<String, Boolean>();        server.getPluginManager().registerEvents(this, this);    }     @EventHandler    public void onPlayerLogin(PlayerLoginEvent event) {        if (greet.containsKey(event.getPlayer().getName())) {            if (greet.get(event.getPlayer().getName())) {                server.broadcastMessage("THIS IS A MESSAGE");            }        }    }}